[03/05/26, 19.18.30] ~ Haroon: Good afternoon Pak Agung

If I may answer

- It is the QR Code that gets blocked forever after the system detects attempts to copy. How? Basically, counterfeiters when they try to copy, they must get the QR data in order to print it. The moment they try to get the QR data, the system detects it and fraudsters will know this fact, detering them from copying.

    So if counterfeiters still *try to* use that QR code on fake products, it will be useless as it is already blocked and they will actually then end up not using it.

    The system blocks it based on many 'anomaly rules' (just like how internet firewall works) and whenever any rule gets triggered, it blocks it. 

   In the video, we are *simulating* that if a QR is scanned multiple times (assuming an attempt of copying), it gets blocked. ‎<This message was edited>
